{"word":"σκυτάλη","slug":"σκυτάλη","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<entryFree id=\"n95347\" key=\"skuta/lh\" type=\"main\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"entryFree\"> <orth extent=\"full\" lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"orth\">σκῠτάλη</orth> [<foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ᾰ], <gen lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"gen\">ἡ</gen></foreign>, <sense id=\"n95347.0\" n=\"A\" level=\"1\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"sense\"> <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">staff, cudgel, club</tr_>, <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0060.tlg001.perseus-grc3:3:8\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ D.S.\">D.S.</a></author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">3.8</biblScope> </bibl>; <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ς. ἀγριέλαιος</foreign>, of Heracles' <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">club,</tr_> <bibl default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\">AP</author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">9.237</biblScope> </bibl> (<bibl default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\">Eryc.</author> </bibl>); cf. <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">σκύταλον</foreign>:—Special usages: </sense> <sense n=\"1\" id=\"n95347.1\" level=\"3\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"sense\"> at Sparta, <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">staff</tr_> or <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">baton</tr_>, used as a cypher for writing dispatches, a strip of leather being rolled slantwise round it, on which the dispatches were written lengthwise, so that when unrolled they were unintelligible: commanders abroad had a staff of <abbr TEIform=\"abbr\">like</abbr> thickness, round which they rolled these strips, and so were able to read the dispatches:—hence <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">σκυτάλη</foreign> came to mean <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">a Spartan dispatch</tr_>, <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0003.tlg001.perseus-grc1:1:131\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Th.\">Th.</a></author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">1.131</biblScope></bibl>, <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0032.tlg001.perseus-grc1:3:3:8\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ X.\">X.</a></author> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ HG\">HG</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">3.3.8</biblScope></bibl>, <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0019.tlg007.perseus-grc1:991\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Ar.\">Ar.</a></author> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Lys.\">Lys.</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">991</biblScope></bibl>, <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0007.tlg032:19\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\">Plu.</author> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Lys.\">Lys.</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">19</biblScope></bibl>, <bibl default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\">Gell.</author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">17.9.15</biblScope> </bibl>; and, generally, <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">dispatch, message</tr_>, as <bibl default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Pi.\">Pi.</a></author> </bibl> calls the bearer of his ode <cit TEIform=\"cit\"> <quote_ lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"quote\">σκυτάλα Μοισᾶν</quote_> <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0033.tlg001.perseus-grc1:6:91\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <title_ TEIform=\"title\">O.</title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">6.91</biblScope></bibl></cit>, where the Sch. quotes <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ἀχνυμένη σκυτάλη</foreign> (dub. sens.) from <bibl default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\">Archil.</author> </bibl> (<bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0232.tlg001:89:2\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Fr.\">Fr.</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">89.2</biblScope> </bibl>); <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ἡ σκυτάλης περιτροπή</foreign>, of labour in vain (cf. <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ὕπερος</foreign>), <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0059.tlg006.perseus-grc1:209d\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Pl.\">Pl.</a></author> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Tht.\">Tht.</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">209d</biblScope></bibl>. </sense> <sense n=\"2\" id=\"n95347.2\" level=\"3\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"sense\"> <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">pole</tr_> or <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">staff</tr_>, <abbr TEIform=\"abbr\">like</abbr> those of a sedan-chair, <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0527.tlg002:30:4\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ LXX\">LXX</a></author> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Ex.\">Ex.</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">30.4</biblScope></bibl>. </sense> <sense n=\"3\" id=\"n95347.3\" level=\"3\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"sense\"> <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">strickle for levelling grain</tr_> piled up in a measure, <cit TEIform=\"cit\"> <quote_ lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"quote\">ς. δικαία</quote_> <bibl n=\"Perseus:abo:pap,P.Tebt.:823:15\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ PTeb.\">PTeb.</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">823.15</biblScope></bibl></cit>, <bibl n=\"Perseus:abo:pap,P.Amh.:2:43:10\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ PAmh.\">PAmh.</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">2.43.10</biblScope> </bibl> (both <date TEIform=\"date\">ii B.C.</date>), cf. <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0542.tlg001:4:170\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\">Poll.</author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">4.170</biblScope></bibl>. </sense> <sense n=\"4\" id=\"n95347.4\" level=\"3\" opt=\"n\"